    "content_hash": "e10e8fd29634d04c",
    "department": "Recruitment / People Ops",
    "description": "Capi http://www.capimoney.com/ is building the financial infrastructure for emerging markets trade.\n\nBacked by $18M+ from top-tier investors like Creandum, Y Combinator, General Catalyst, and angels from Revolut, Checkout, Stripe, and Remitly, we’re building the financial infrastructure that emerging markets deserve.\n\nOur mission is to grow GDP in emerging markets by making the global financial system fairer and more accessible. We’re tackling global trade, making it easier for importers to pay their international suppliers. Our platform enables businesses to expand rapidly, create jobs, and be engines of prosperity for their countries.\n\nOur team is made up of approx 100 people across 10 countries; we are a group of a highly-ambitious, get-it-done people, who like to work hard on something that has a tangible impact in the world. And we’re looking for more people to join our team!\n\nTake a look through Capi’s mission \u0026 values. https://capimoney.com/mission-and-values\n\n\nTHE ROLE\n\nWe're looking for a proactive and creative operator to join our team as our first in-market People Ops hire. Based in Dakar, you'll support the employee lifecycle not only for Capi Senegal, but also Cameroon, Côte d’Ivoire, Congo, Mali, Kenya, Benin, Togo, and additional markets as we grow!\n\nYou'll be the friendly face and trusted point-of-contact for new joiners across Francophone and Anglophone African markets, ensuring fast, smooth, compliant onboarding and an outstanding employee experience.\n\nThis is a rare opportunity to help shape the foundations of People Operations across multiple countries and build scalable systems from the ground up.\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO\n\n - Regional People Operations\n   \n   - Serve as the primary People Ops contact for team members across Senegal, CIV, Mali, Kenya, Benin, Togo, and future markets.\n   \n   - Partner with local HR teams through our EOR platforms to ensure compliance with employment laws across multiple jurisdictions.\n   \n   - Coordinate local policies (leave, benefits, contracts) with support from the Head of People.\n\n - Onboarding \u0026 Offboarding Excellence\n   \n   - Lead onboarding for all hires across West and East Africa, including scheduling, equipment provision, orientation, systems access, and documentation.\n   \n   - Work with recruiters and managers to ensure new joiners feel supported, informed, and fully equipped from the start.\n   \n   - Maintain consistent onboarding standards across markets (checklists, communication templates, welcome guides).\n   \n   - Manage offboarding workflows, exit documentation, and knowledge transfer.\n\n - Payroll, Benefits \u0026 Admin\n   \n   - Respond to employee questions about payroll, benefits, and leave rules with clarity and empathy.\n   \n   - Coordinate closely with our EOR partners Deel and Rivermate.\n   \n   - Support health insurance administration, reimbursements, and local statutory requirements.\n\n - Office Support (Senegal HQ)\n   \n   - Support office operations in Dakar: supplies, equipment coordination, vendor management, and event support.\n   \n   - Coordinate local team gatherings, market visits, and offsites.\n   \n   - Champion Capi’s culture across a distributed team and help build strong connections between markets.\n\n - People Systems \u0026 Process Improvement\n   \n   - Manage employee records, contracts, letters, and compliance documentation.\n   \n   - Help develop scalable People processes and SOPs across onboarding, leave, travel, employee events, and more.\n   \n   - Identify operational bottlenecks and propose improvements to enhance speed and quality of People support.\n\n\nWHO YOU ARE\n\n - Must-haves\n   \n   - 4+ years in People Operations, HR, Office Management, or a similar operational role.\n   \n   - Strong organisational skills that make you able to coordinate across teams and countries without dropping details.\n   \n   - Excellent people and communication skills; you are approachable and solutions-oriented.\n   \n   - Comfortable navigating ambiguity and building structure where none exists.\n   \n   - Fluent in French and English (written and spoken).\n   \n   - Based in Dakar, with the ability to work from the Dakar office several days a week.\n\n - Nice-to-haves\n   \n   - Experience supporting operations across multiple African markets.\n   \n   - Knowledge of local labour regulations (Senegal or other WAEMU countries).\n   \n   - Experience in a startup or high-growth environment.\n   \n   - Familiarity with HRIS tools, payroll tools, or Google Workspace.\n\n\nWHAT SUCCESS LOOKS LIKE AFTER 6 MONTHS\n\n - New hires consistently report a smooth, welcoming onboarding experience.\n\n - Market-specific People processes (contracts, benefits, payroll inputs) are reliable and timely.\n\n - Office operations in Dakar run smoothly and predictably.\n\n - Managers trust you as a dependable partner who helps them execute quickly and compliantly.\n\n - You’ve helped create clearer SOPs and introduced efficiency into People workflows.\n\n\nWHY JOIN CAPI\n\n - Help build a world-class People Operations function across multiple African markets.\n\n - Work closely with a small, mission-driven team shaping financial access across the continent.\n\n - Grow quickly - this role could scale into a senior People Operations position as the company expands.\n\nCapi is an equal opportunity employer and welcomes candidates from diverse backgrounds. We’re all about building a diverse, inclusive team at Capi. Whoever you are, we’d love to hear from you. If there’s anything you need to make the interview process easier—whether it’s accessibility support, a different format, or just a heads-up about what to expect—just let us know, we’re happy to help.\n\nWe've won some cool awards recently too! Check them out:\n\n - Startups UK Top 100 (No. 24) https://startups.co.uk/startups-100/2026/capi-money/\n\n - Viva Technology Top 100 https://vivatechnology.com/top-100-rising-european-startups\n\n - Welcome to the Jungle's Fintech's Finest Top 50 https://employers.welcometothejungle.com/fintechs-finest-50",
